''so i'd rather just stay up here on your warm and cozy head. ''  i screamed at him and said that he was silly , and he needed to get off.   he said, ''look for yourself!'' i flipped on the light, and looked under my bed.   ''aaaahhh!'' there really are fifteen hundered rattle snakes just beneath my bed!''   my mom called to me and said, ''don't   scream , it's saturday , sleep in!''  still i yelled and yelled.  my brother came up and laughed.    he said, ''april fools!''  ''the fifteen hundered rattle snakes are pieces of rope with googly eyes, '' my brother said. text: it's lunch time now and i don't know what to do,   i lost my lunch and they're serving gloop,  i'm the next in line and plop!  the gloop is on my tray.  i'm trying it,  well here goes: munch. . . . .  aarrrggghh; this is gross! i found my lunch!!

title: Birds!
author: harold
text: birds are cute as i mute the t. v.  i watch the birds  as they watch me birds can be nice as they eat mice birds aren't always nice as they also eat lice.

title: Who Knew I Liked Chickens
author: harold
text: who knew i liked chickens,  it's raining chickens,  all over my hair,  chickens can be funny,  but not if they call mummy,  who knew i liked chickens? nobody knows.

title: The clock goes tick tock
author: harper
text: i spy a clock,  that goes tick tock,  it needs some batterys,  and some calaries,  one day it will go to sleep,  it has to leap,  a few quick heaps,  with a bundle of hay,  it says yay,  on the day,  the chicken lays,  in the way,  of the farmers hay,  in the middle of may,  down by the bay.

title: the ights
author: harper
text: i spy a light,  having a flight doing things right and tying things tight

author: harriet
text: the time is gone

title: The big giant tomato
author: harrison
text: one day i wanted to grow a tomato plant. i went to get some seeds but i forgot to dig.  so i went to go dig. then i went to go get the seeds. i put the seeds in the hole and buried the seeds. then i went to go get some water. when i came back. . . it was the bigest  tomato i've ever seen!!!for dinner that same night i invited everybody in the naborhood for tomato soup. tomorrow i want to grow a pumpkin plant tomorrow.

title: MY MOM
author: harrison
text: my mom is the best.  my mom is very care giving.  i'm sure yours is to.

title: Birds
author: harrison
text: aren't birds so cool,   bathing in a pool.  can one bird top the rest,  ducks can sometimes be the best.  eagles aren't so nice ,  finding them eating mice

title: Base Ball
author: harrison
text: i love base ball more than anything.  i`ll keep base ball under my wing.  every single day.

title: Chase C.
author: harrison
text: chase c.  is my friend.   he loves to play basketball.   chase c.  is very,  very,  smart.   that is my friend chase c.

title: May I have Your Attention Please
author: harrison
text: b--e--e--p danger! danger! high voltage! go inside,  stay away.  please do not be fooled! it goes clap,  clap. . .  it goes zap,  zap.  it may be shocking,  could this be doom? have you seen it???   it's lightning!

title: Car Chase
author: harrison
text: there was a bad guy in a car,  that stole a chocolate bar,  from his favorite gangster bar,   there was policemen chasing him,  also army men ,  and a farmer with a cotton gin ,   the chase was still going on ,  then a boy called don called his mom,  then his mom came out with a gun,  and shot the back of his ford f150,   then lost control ,  then popped his mole,  then crashed into a hole,  and then flew into a bunch of coal .   harrison m ,  fairyland school,  georgia

title: The City
author: harrison
text: i hear people talking  blah blah blah  i hear loud noises everywhere i look  aah clang honk  i see cars too,  zoom zoom zoom i see street lights and street signs there are stores side  to side  ring,  ring,  ring.

title: Cyclone
author: harrison
text: the cyclone spins round and round everything moves all a round.  it races in fast as it can twirling everything around.  cows are flying, there's a car then a tree,  and a house.  barnyard torn like paper tractors thrown and plows.  it's coming for you like a gun.  it's a cyclone and you know it.  whipping winds like a flag.  everybody run!
